description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Practice Education F&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;a&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;cilitator - Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 37.5hrs./wk. This a full time post (part time will be considered)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract: -12-month fixed term contract&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;T&lt;/strong&gt;he Trust has an ambitious goal to increase the number of student nurses and midwives that the Trust can train.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, and experienced registered nurse, with excellent planning and organisational skills to deliver a specific project to expand nursing and midwifery student placement capacity across the Trust. They will work closely with Practice Education Facilitators (PEFs) to deliver this project over a one year fixed term contract&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main emphasis of this role will be work in partnership with nursing, midwifery and allied health care teams to expand the number of nursing placements and implement innovative models of support for learners such as Collaborative Learning in Practice (CLiP) and virtual learning placements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This a temporary full time post (part time will be considered) The successful applicant will possess:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• NMC registration for a minimum of 3 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Masters of First degree health related subject or equivalent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Approved NMC Mentor qualification and a good understanding of nurse training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience of Leadership at Band 6 or above or equivalent and working autonomously and engaging others in projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Must be a self-starter and able to accept responsibility for own project work, working under own initiative and within boundaries of role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information and expressions of interest please contact: Linda Chapman, Education Lead Nurse on 01225 824583 l.chapman1@nhs.net or Ana Gleghorn Associate Director of Nursing &amp; Midwifery a.gleghorn@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on Thursday 19th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
